From 3e0467e6c38ece9c43aa67b83cd133189e774098 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <localbot-claude@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 20:47:18 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: --flash-attn requires explicit value on llama.cpp b9xxx+
 builds
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The Dockerfile pins LLAMA_VERSION=b9592 (released 2026-06-10). Recent
llama-server builds changed --flash-attn from a bare boolean flag to
an enum requiring an explicit value:

    -fa, --flash-attn [on|off|auto]   (default: auto)

The bare --flash-attn in LLAMA_SERVER_EXTRA_ARGS fails argument parsing
on these builds and crashes llama-server immediately on startup:

    RuntimeError: llama-server exited unexpectedly (exit code 1)
    after 1 health-check attempt(s)

Fix: use --flash-attn on explicitly in .env.example and README.

Using 'on' rather than 'auto' deliberately — quantized V-cache
(--cache-type-v q8_0) requires flash attention to actually be active;
'auto' leaves that decision to the binary at runtime and risks a
separate 'V cache quantization requires flash_attn' failure if it
decides not to enable it.

Affected: .env.example, README.md (Performance Tuning + Speculative
Decoding sections), docker-compose.yml (tuning comment block).
---
 .env.example       | 2 +-
 README.md          | 4 ++--
 docker-compose.yml | 7 +++++--
 3 files changed, 8 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/.env.example b/.env.example
index e6b3355..8410bcf 100644
--- a/.env.example
+++ b/.env.example
@@ -83,7 +83,7 @@ LLAMA_CTX_SIZE=2048
 # for the i5-10400H and are applied by docker-compose.yml.
 # To enable speculative decoding, add:
 #   --model-draft /models/your-draft-model-q4_k_m.gguf --draft-max 5 --draft-min 1
-LLAMA_SERVER_EXTRA_ARGS=--flash-attn --cache-type-k q8_0 --cache-type-v q8_0 --ubatch-size 512
+LLAMA_SERVER_EXTRA_ARGS=--flash-attn on --cache-type-k q8_0 --cache-type-v q8_0 --ubatch-size 512
 
 # ── Sandbox ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 # Absolute path INSIDE the container that the filesystem tools are confined to.
diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
index 49f9fda..67b7c29 100644
--- a/README.md
+++ b/README.md
@@ -214,7 +214,7 @@ The following extra args are set via `LLAMA_SERVER_EXTRA_ARGS` in `.env`:
 
 | Flag | Effect |
 |---|---|
-| `--flash-attn` | O(n) attention memory vs O(n²); cuts TTFT ~15–25% as history accumulates |
+| `--flash-attn on` | O(n) attention memory vs O(n²); cuts TTFT ~15–25% as history accumulates. Note: recent llama.cpp builds (b9xxx+) require an explicit value — `on`/`off`/`auto` — bare `--flash-attn` will fail to parse and crash the server on startup |
 | `--cache-type-k q8_0` | 8-bit KV key cache; frees ~200–500 MB with negligible quality delta |
 | `--cache-type-v q8_0` | 8-bit KV value cache |
 | `--ubatch-size 512` | Micro-batch size for parallel prompt evaluation |
@@ -226,7 +226,7 @@ Speculative decoding uses a small, fast draft model to generate candidate tokens
 ```env
 # .env
 SLOT_DRAFT_MODEL=/models/qwen2.5-0.5b-instruct-q4_k_m.gguf
-LLAMA_SERVER_EXTRA_ARGS=--flash-attn --cache-type-k q8_0 --cache-type-v q8_0 --ubatch-size 512 --model-draft /models/qwen2.5-0.5b-instruct-q4_k_m.gguf --draft-max 5 --draft-min 1
+LLAMA_SERVER_EXTRA_ARGS=--flash-attn on --cache-type-k q8_0 --cache-type-v q8_0 --ubatch-size 512 --model-draft /models/qwen2.5-0.5b-instruct-q4_k_m.gguf --draft-max 5 --draft-min 1
 ```
 
 RAM budget with speculative decoding on 16 GB:
diff --git a/docker-compose.yml b/docker-compose.yml
index b45f945..41d85a3 100644
--- a/docker-compose.yml
+++ b/docker-compose.yml
@@ -26,8 +26,11 @@
 #   - LLAMA_ARG_MMAP=true            → memory-map model file; fast cold start, lower RSS
 #
 # Extra args passed via LLAMA_SERVER_EXTRA_ARGS (set in .env or override here):
-#   --flash-attn                     → O(n) attention memory vs O(n²); cuts TTFT ~15-25% for
-#                                       accumulated history; required for ctx > 2048
+#   --flash-attn on                  → O(n) attention memory vs O(n²); cuts TTFT ~15-25% for
+#                                       accumulated history; required for ctx > 2048.
+#                                       NOTE: must pass an explicit value (on/off/auto) on
+#                                       llama.cpp builds b9xxx+ — bare --flash-attn will fail
+#                                       to parse and crash llama-server on startup.
 #   --cache-type-k q8_0              → 8-bit KV key cache; frees ~200-500 MB RAM vs fp16
 #   --cache-type-v q8_0              → 8-bit KV value cache; negligible quality delta
 #   --ubatch-size 512                → micro-batch for parallel prompt evaluation
-- 
2.43.0

